---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import ProjectCard from '../components/ProjectCard.astro';
import LearningCard from '../components/LearningCard.astro';
import { projects } from '../data/projects';
import { learningPaths } from '../data/learningPaths';
const featuredPath = learningPaths[0];
---
<SiteLayout current="home">
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Backend engineering lab</p>
    <h1>I design backend systems where boundaries, trade-offs, and evolution paths are explicit.</h1>
    <p class="lede">The work here favors explicit models, small durable APIs, decision records, and documentation that makes trade-offs visible.</p>
    <dl class="hero-metadata">
      <div><dt>Home base</dt><dd>.NET</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Current mode</dt><dd>active experiments, evolving in public</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Evidence</dt><dd>docs, ADRs, examples</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Output</dt><dd>projects and learning paths</dd></div>
    </dl>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="button button-library" href="/projects/">View projects</a>
      <a class="button button-learning" href="/learning-paths/">Explore learning paths</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Behind the lab</p>
      <h2>Behind the lab</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="panel prose-panel">
      <p>I’m Simon Gelbart, a .NET-focused backend developer in France with experience building and maintaining backend systems.</p>
      <p>This site is my public engineering lab: a place where I use projects and learning material to think through backend architecture, modeling, documentation, and tooling.</p>
      <p>Most of the work starts from the .NET ecosystem, but the questions are broader than one stack.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="/about.html">Read more about the lab →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Active experiments</p>
      <h2>Active experiments</h2>
      <p>Each project starts from a practical need, a technical idea, or a design pressure worth exploring through code and documentation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="project-grid">
      {projects.map((project) => <ProjectCard project={project} />)}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-compact">
    <div class="note">These projects — and this site around them — are active experiments. Some parts are usable, some are rough, and the shape of the lab will evolve as the work becomes clearer.</div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">How I work</p>
      <h2>How I work</h2>
      <p>The details change from project to project, but the same habits show up in the work.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-grid">
      <article class="card principle"><h3>Explicit boundaries</h3><p>I prefer systems where responsibilities, contracts, and failure modes are visible before they become bugs.</p><p class="meta-line">Seen in: Pattrn package boundaries · LORQ adapter contracts</p></article>
      <article class="card principle"><h3>Visible trade-offs</h3><p>I trust designs more when the cost of a decision is written down, not hidden in code or memory.</p><p class="meta-line">Seen in: ADRs · design notes</p></article>
      <article class="card principle"><h3>Evidence over claims</h3><p>I want projects to show their reasoning through docs, tests, ADRs, examples, or reproducible outputs.</p><p class="meta-line">Seen in: LORQ reports · learning exercises</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Learning as another output</p>
      <h2>Learning as another output</h2>
      <p>Some ideas become libraries or tools. Others become lessons, examples, and decision guides.</p>
    </div>
    <LearningCard path={featuredPath} featured />
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading"><h2>Explore next</h2></div>
    <div class="explore-grid">
      <a class="surface" href="/projects/"><strong>Projects</strong><span>See what is being built.</span></a>
      <a class="surface" href="/learning-paths/"><strong>Learning paths</strong><span>See what is being taught.</span></a>
      <a class="surface" href="/about.html"><strong>About</strong><span>Understand the lab.</span></a>
      <a class="surface" href="https://github.com/SimonGelbart" rel="noreferrer"><strong>GitHub ↗</strong><span>Inspect the source.</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
